bs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"best wordpress books\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"professional wordpress books\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"wordpress books\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21:\"wordpress for dummies\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"wordpress to go\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"https://www.isitwp.com/?p=232118\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:613:\"<p>Are you looking for the best WordPress books to read this year? Books are always helpful for self-paced learning and quickly acquiring valuable knowledge from experts. When it comes to WordPress, there are hundreds, even thousands, of books on the market. With so much potential reading material to choose from, it can be difficult to [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-books/\">10 Best WordPress Books You&#8217;ll Want to Read in 2019</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Editorial Team\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17905:\"<p>Are you looking for the best WordPress books to read this year?</p>\n<p>Books are always helpful for self-paced learning and quickly acquiring valuable knowledge from experts. When it comes to WordPress, there are hundreds, even thousands, of books on the market. With so much potential reading material to choose from, it can be difficult to know where to start. </p>\n<p>That&#8217;s why we hit the stacks, did the reading, and narrowed down your selection to the 10 absolute best WordPress books for 2019. </p>\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll share the WordPress books that we feel bring the most to the table. These books are sure to increase your skill level. You&#8217;re going to want to read these; trust us.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wordpress-dummies-book/\" title=\"WordPress All-in-One For Dummies\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">1. WordPress All-in-One For Dummies</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wordpress-dummies-book/\" title=\"WordPress All-in-One For Dummies\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpdummiesbook.png\" alt=\"WordPress All-in-One-For Dummies\" width=\"775\" height=\"350\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232124\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpdummiesbook.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpdummiesbook-300x135.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpdummiesbook-768x347.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>WordPress All-in-One For Dummies is a very popular WordPress book this year, and for good reason. It includes a pack of 8 mini books which offer easy-to-understand information on basic WordPress topics. This book tackles multiple topics including SEO, social media, WordPress plugin development, and <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/install-setup-wordpress-multisite-network/\" title=\"How to Install and Set Up WordPress Multisite Network\">multisite networks</a>.</p>\n<p>It provides a simple overview of WordPress and is great for beginners who want a truly &#8216;all-in-one&#8217; resource at their fingertips. It&#8217;s also a good read for intermediate to advanced users who need to brush up their skills in a few key areas. </p>\n<p>The &#8216;Dummies&#8217; franchise is known for tackling a variety of educational topics in a light-hearted way. The occasional sprinkling of humor throughout the book keeps even the most technical aspects from seeming too dense or difficult. You&#8217;ll learn handy tips, techniques, and advice on how to use WordPress the right way in a language you can understand.</p>\n<p><strong>Authors:</strong> Originally written by Lisa Sabin Wilson with contributions by Michael Torbert, Andrea Rennick, Cory Miller, and Kevin Palmer.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/professional-wordpress-book/\" title=\"Professional WordPress: Design and Development\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">2. Professional WordPress: Design and Development</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/professional-wordpress-book/\" title=\"Professional WordPress: Design and Development\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/professionwpbook.png\" alt=\"Professional WordPress Design and Development\" width=\"775\" height=\"350\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232123\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/professionwpbook.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/professionwpbook-300x135.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/professionwpbook-768x347.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re looking for a book on learning development processes, then check out Professional WordPress. This book covers most of the newest development and coding techniques, and they&#8217;ve included up-to-date screenshots (until WordPress 4.1 version). It talks about key concepts and uses real websites examples that are actively using WordPress.</p>\n<p>It also talks about migrating your website to WordPress. The book discusses the latest tools and techniques that you can apply to <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-make-a-website-step-by-step/\" title=\"How to Make a Website - Step by Step (with Pictures)\">create a website with WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Authors:</strong> Brad Williams, Hal Stern, and David Damstra</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wordpress-go-book/\" title=\"WordPress To Go\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">3. WordPress To Go</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wordpress-go-book/\" title=\"WordPress To Go\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wptogobook.png\" alt=\"WordPress to go\" width=\"775\" height=\"350\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232132\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wptogobook.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wptogobook-300x135.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wptogobook-768x347.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>As the name suggests, WordPress To Go is a book on building your website or blog with WordPress on the go. It covers the basic steps: from <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/domain-name-work/\" title=\"What is a Domain Name and How Does it Work? (Explained)\">purchasing a domain name</a>, to getting a <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/hosting-reviews/wordpress/\" title=\"The Best WordPress Hosting Companies (Real Reviews, No B.S)\">WordPress hosting</a> account, to <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/install-wordpress-complete-wordpress-installation-tutorial/\" title=\"How to Install WordPress – The Complete WordPress Installation Tutorial\">installing WordPress</a>. It also shares how to <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-create-an-online-store-step-by-step/\" title=\"How to Create an Online Store – Step by Step (with Pictures)\">create an eCommerce store</a>.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, it&#8217;ll guide you on how to start adding content onto your website and using images in a professional way. This book also shares the author&#8217;s <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/top-wordpress-plugins/\" title=\"27 Best WordPress Plugins that You MUST Use\">must-have WordPress plugins</a>, themes, and other useful tools.</p>\n<p><strong>Author:</strong> Sarah McHarry</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wordpress-missing-manual-book/\" title=\"WordPress: The Missing Manual\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">4. WordPress: The Missing Manual</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wordpress-missing-manual-book/\" title=\"WordPress: The Missing Manual\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpmissingmanualsbook.png\" alt=\"WordPress the Missing Manuals\" width=\"775\" height=\"350\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232131\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpmissingmanualsbook.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpmissingmanualsbook-300x135.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpmissingmanualsbook-768x347.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>WordPress: The Missing Manual is an excellent book with instructions for creating all types of websites, <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-start-a-blog-step-by-step/\" title=\"How to Start a WordPress Blog (&#038; Make Extra Income)\">blogs</a>, and eCommerce stores. It discusses the use of correct widgets for each type of website, adding necessary features, and designing your website to look professional.</p>\n<p>This book shares useful tips on <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/seo-friendly/\" title=\"How to Make Your WordPress Site SEO Friendly\">SEO optimization</a> and how to make your website responsive. You can also learn about creating image galleries, slideshows, video clips, and more.</p>\n<p><strong>Author: Matthew MacDonald</strong></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wordpress-easy-steps-book/\" title=\"WordPress in Easy Steps\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">5. WordPress in Easy Steps</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wordpress-easy-steps-book/\" title=\"WordPress in Easy Steps\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpeasystepsbook.png\" alt=\"WordPress in Easy Steps\" width=\"775\" height=\"350\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232130\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpeasystepsbook.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpeasystepsbook-300x135.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpeasystepsbook-768x347.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>WordPress in Easy Steps is a complete book on setting up your WordPress site. It covers important starter topics including managing your WordPress dashboard, adding new content, changing the appearance of your site, plugins, comments, and more. This book also discusses using the settings and tools within WordPress.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s written for bloggers, developers, or anyone using WordPress. The book shares tricks and tips to improve the performance of your site. It&#8217;s a good read for this year, especially if you&#8217;re just getting started.</p>\n<p><strong>Author:</strong> Darryl Bartlett</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wordpress-beginners-book/\" title=\"WordPress For Beginners: A Visual Guide to Building Your WordPress Site\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">6. WordPress For Beginners: A Visual Guide to Building Your WordPress Site</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wordpress-beginners-book/\" title=\"WordPress for Beginners: A Visual Guide to Building Your WordPress Site\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforbeginnersbook.png\" alt=\"WordPress for Beginners\" width=\"775\" height=\"350\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232129\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforbeginnersbook.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforbeginnersbook-300x135.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpforbeginnersbook-768x347.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>WordPress for Beginners is the latest book on creating professional and responsive WordPress sites. It takes a visual approach to explain the steps involved with website development with WordPress. The important topics discussed in this book include how to create a free website, <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/how-to-register-a-domain-name/\" title=\"Beginner’s Guide: How to Register a Domain Name (+ Tip on How to Get It for FREE)\">how to register a domain name</a>, how to get <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/hosting-reviews/\" title=\"Top 10 Web Hosting Companies (Real Reviews, No B.S)\">web hosting</a>, and how to install WordPress.</p>\n<p>Aside from that, it shares multiple useful tools to discover the resources used on other WordPress sites. This book also talks about how to <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-backup-plugins-compared/\" title=\"9 Best WordPress Backup Plugins Compared\">create a backup</a> and restore your website in WordPress.</p>\n<p><strong>Author:</strong> Nathan George</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/building-web-apps-wordpress-book/\" title=\"Building Web Apps with WordPress\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">7. Building Web Apps with WordPress</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/building-web-apps-wordpress-book/\" title=\"Building Web Apps with WordPress\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/buildingwebappswpbook.png\" alt=\"Building web apps with WordPress\" width=\"775\" height=\"350\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232128\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/buildingwebappswpbook.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/buildingwebappswpbook-300x135.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/buildingwebappswpbook-768x347.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Building Web Apps with WordPress takes a new approach by comparing the WordPress core with popular app development frameworks. It&#8217;s an advanced WordPress book, sharing knowledge on using themes for appearance and plugins for the backend functionality of your apps.</p>\n<p>It explains, in simple terms, how to create powerful and scalable web apps, mobile applications, web services, and WordPress multisite networks. The book was written for advanced users and developers.</p>\n<p><strong>Authors:</strong> Brian Messenlehner and Jason Coleman</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wordpress-pushing-limits-book/\" title=\"WordPress: Pushing the Limits\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">8. WordPress: Pushing the Limits</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wordpress-pushing-limits-book/\" title=\"WordPress: Pushing the Limits\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wppushinglimitsbook.png\" alt=\"WordPress Pushing the Limits\" width=\"775\" height=\"350\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232127\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wppushinglimitsbook.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wppushinglimitsbook-300x135.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wppushinglimitsbook-768x347.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>This book discusses unique approaches to create a WordPress site that is professional and beautiful. WordPress: Pushing the Limits covers topics like theme development, web hosting, and contingency planning.</p>\n<p>This book shares insight into programming languages like HTML, PHP, JavaScript, etc. It&#8217;s packed with experiences from veteran WordPress developers, explaining how you can succeed with your projects.</p>\n<p><strong>Author:</strong> Rachel McCollin</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/head-first-wordpress-book/\" title=\"Head First WordPress\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">9. Head First WordPress</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/head-first-wordpress-book/\" title=\"Head First WordPress\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/headfirstwpbook.png\" alt=\"Head First WordPress\" width=\"775\" height=\"350\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232126\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/headfirstwpbook.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/headfirstwpbook-300x135.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/headfirstwpbook-768x347.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Head First WordPress is an outstanding book focusing on customizing your website or blog. It shares tips and techniques to design your blog for user engagement and attention. It suggests prominent WordPress themes for quickly selecting of your website&#8217;s template.</p>\n<p>The notable topics covered in the book are how to convert a custom HTML/CSS design into a professional WordPress theme, how to extend the functionality of a plugin, and how to set up databases. The book also talks about basic topics like the difference between tags and categories.</p>\n<p><strong>Author:</strong> Jeff Siarto</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wordpress-websites-business-book/\" title=\"WordPress Websites for Business\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">10. WordPress Websites for Business</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/wordpress-websites-business-book/\" title=\"WordPress Websites for Business\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpwebsiteforbusinessbook.png\" alt=\"WordPress websites for business\" width=\"775\" height=\"350\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-232125\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpwebsiteforbusinessbook.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpwebsiteforbusinessbook-300x135.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/wpwebsiteforbusinessbook-768x347.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>WordPress Websites for Business is a resourceful book offering checklists for building a website. The book includes tips and tricks on simple WordPress settings that can make a major difference in your website&#8217;s performance. It guides you on how to choose the perfect WordPress themes and plugins for your needs.</p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll also discover many content creation hacks in this book. It explains the best practices for creating child themes in WordPress. The book is for all types of WordPress users, from beginners to advanced developers. It&#8217;s also a good read for businesses or <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/popular-big-name-brands-using-wordpress/\" title=\"46 Biggest Brands in the World Using WordPress Actively\">brands using WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Author:</strong> Michael Cordova</p>\n<p>That&#8217;s all.</p>\n<p>We hope this article has helped you find the best WordPress books to read this year. You may also want to check out expert picks of the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-business-phone-services/\" title=\"10 Best Business Phone Services and Systems\">best business phone services and systems</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-books/\">10 Best WordPress Books You&#8217;ll Want to Read in 2019</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-books/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"9 Best Google AdSense Alternatives to Monetize Your Website\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-google-adsense-alternatives/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-google-adsense-alternatives/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s