insights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Sunita Rai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7685:\"<p>Do you want to know the difference between domain and hosting? Wondering why these two often come together? Most beginners have these thoughts, while some even don’t know that they’re separate things. </p>\n<p>That’s mainly because domain name and web hosting are required together to set up a website. However, they’re not one thing. </p>\n<p>In this article, we’ll explain what domain and hosting are, how they work, and how they are different from one another. </p>\n<h3>What is a Domain Name?</h3>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/domainname.png\" alt=\"What Is a Domain Name\" width=\"620\" height=\"361\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-199526\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/domainname.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/domainname-300x175.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>A domain name is your website’s address on the internet where people can access your website. It is something that internet users type in the browser’s URL bar to visit your site. </p>\n<p>For example, the domain name of our website is monsterinsights.com. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/monsterinsightsdomainname.png\" alt=\"MonsterInsights Domain Name\" width=\"620\" height=\"173\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-199527\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/monsterinsightsdomainname.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/monsterinsightsdomainname-300x84.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Domain names have mainly two parts separated by a dot. The first part is your brand name which can have any combination of letters and numbers, like MonsterInsights, whereas the second part is a domain extension like .com, .org, .net, .com.uk, etc.  </p>\n<p>Each domain is a unique web address. This means that there can be only one monsterinsights.com in the world. </p>\n<h3>What is a Web Hosting?</h3>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/websitehosting.png\" alt=\"What is Web Hosting\" width=\"620\" height=\"343\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-199532\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/websitehosting.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/websitehosting-300x166.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Web hosting is the storage location where your website content files are placed. It’s like the home of your website. </p>\n<p>If your domain name was the address of your house, then the actual house is your hosting server. You need both a domain name and web hosting to create a website. </p>\n<p>When a user tries to access your website by entering your web address (domain name) in the browser’s URL bar, the domain name points them to the files stored in the web server. Then, they can see your website online.</p>\n<h3>Domain Name vs Web Hosting – What’s the Difference?</h3>\n<p>Domain names and web hosting are two different things; however, they’re closely connected. You need both a domain name and a web hosting account to create a website. This means that you can’t build a website without any one of them. </p>\n<p>To get started, you can choose a domain name and register it with a domain registrar company. With most domain companies, you can register a domain name for a minimum period of 1 year. You need to renew your domain before expiring to continue using it. </p>\n<p>Next, you can buy a hosting plan and link it with your domain name. After that, you can install a website software (for example, WordPress), install tools and plugins, and add content to your website.  </p>\n<h3>Can I Buy Domain and Hosting from the Same Company?</h3>\n<p>Yes, you can. You can buy a domain and a hosting account from the same company or from different companies. </p>\n<p>If you buy both a domain and hosting from the same company, the setup process becomes a bit easier as you don’t need to change the domain name settings. That is why many companies have started offering both the services together.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bluehost</a> is one of such companies that offers both domain and hosting services at a reasonable cost. It’s offering an exclusive deal for WordPress users which provides you a free domain name at the purchase of any WordPress hosting plan. </p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/bluehostwordpresshosting.jpg\" alt=\"Bluehost Best WordPress Hosting\" width=\"620\" height=\"375\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-185172\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/bluehostwordpresshosting.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/bluehostwordpresshosting-300x181.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Typically, a domain name costs $14.99 / year, and a web hosting plan costs around $7.99 / month. However, Bluehost WordPress hosting deal allows you to buy hosting as low as $2.75 / month which is a 60% off on the usual price. It also gives you a free domain name and free SSL certificate. </p>\n<p>Using Bluehost not only makes the website setup process easy, but it also saves plenty of your money. </p>\n<p>If you want to register a domain name from a different domain company, you can register with one of these top domain registration companies. </p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/domain-com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Domain.com</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/godaddy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">GoDaddy</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/namecheap/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">NameCheap</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/dreamhost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">DreamHost</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>And, if you want Bluehost alternatives for web hosting, you can buy from one of the following top hosting companies. </p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/siteground/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">SiteGround</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/hostgator/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">HostGator</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/inmotion-hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">InMotion Hosting</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>We hope this article helped to understand the difference between the domain name and hosting. You may also want to see our guide on <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-free-business-email-address/\">how to create a free business email address</a>.</p>\n<p>If you liked this article, then please subscribe to our <a href=\"http://youtube.com/wpbeginner?sub_confirmation=1\" title=\"WPBeginner on YouTube\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">YouTube Channel</a> for WordPress video tutorials. You can also find us on <a href=\"http://twitter.com/wpbeginner\" title=\"WPBeginner on Twitter\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/wpbeginner\" title=\"WPBeginner on Facebook\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Facebook</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/whats-the-difference-between-domain-and-hosting-beginners-guide/\">What&#8217;s the Difference Between Domain and Hosting? (Beginner&#8217;s Guide)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:101:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/whats-the-difference-between-domain-and-hosting-beginners-guide/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"Announcing Scroll Tracking, Front-End Page Insights, and More\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:195:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/announcing-scroll-tracking-front-end-page-insights-and-more/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=announcing-scroll-tracking-front-end-page-insights-and-more\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:100:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/announcing-scroll-tracking-front-end-page-insights-and-more/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 30 Apr 2019 12:39:00 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:3:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Announcements\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"page insights\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"scroll tracking\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/?p=199029\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:618:\"<p>Ever wish you could see how people are truly interacting with your website? Sessions and bounce rates only tell you so much. How much of your content are they really reading? With the latest release of MonsterInsights, now you can see how far people are scrolling on your website, so you can get a better [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/announcing-scroll-tracking-front-end-page-insights-and-more/\">Announcing Scroll Tracking, Front-End Page Insights, and More</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Keri Engel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5173:\"<p>Ever wish you could see how people are truly interacting with your website? Sessions and bounce rates only tell you so much. How much of your content are they really reading?</p>\n<p>With the latest release of MonsterInsights, now you can see how far people are scrolling on your website, so you can get a better picture of your visitor engagement and make data-driven decisions to grow your business.</p>\n<p>Let’s take a closer look at what’s new in MonsterInsights 7.6&#8230;</p>\n<h3>New Automatic Scroll Tracking</h3>\n<p>Google Analytics has no automatic, native way to set up scroll tracking. But MonsterInsights 7.6 will automatically enable this feature for you &#8211; no setup or configuration required.</p>\n<p>Your scroll tracking stats can be found in the MonsterInsights Publishers Report, next to the Interests section.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/scroll-tracking-in-wordpress.jpg\" alt=\"scroll tracking in wordpress with monsterinsights\" width=\"560\" height=\"324\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-199030\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/scroll-tracking-in-wordpress.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/scroll-tracking-in-wordpress-300x174.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>Scroll tracking can not only give you a better picture of how your visitors are interacting with your content, but also help you decide the best place for your important <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-create-the-perfect-call-to-action/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">calls to action</a>, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-adsense-in-google-analytics-to-optimize-your-revenue/\">ads</a>, and more.</p>\n<p>Read our <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/docs/scroll-tracking-and-reporting/\">scroll tracking documentation</a> for details on how to use Scroll Tracking and view scroll percentage for each page.</p>\n<h3>View Page Insights on the Front End of Your Site</h3>\n<p>MonsterInsights 7.6 includes a new feature call Admin Bar Page Insights</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/front-end-page-insights-min.jpg\" alt=\"front end page insights for wordpress using monsterinsights\" width=\"560\" height=\"330\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-199033\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/front-end-page-insights-min.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/front-end-page-insights-min-300x177.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>Now you can easily see your last 30 day stats for any page at a glance.</p>\n<p>This will make it easier than ever to make content decisions quickly, without having to spend a lot of time generating reports in Google Analytics. Seeing your page stats at a glance will help you:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>come up with content ideas based on what your audience loves</li>\n<li>decide which content needs to be deleted or optimized to boost your traffic</li>\n<li>create the products and premium offerings your visitors are looking for</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You can view our <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/docs/admin-bar-page-insights/\">admin bar page insights doc</a> for more details.</p>\n<h3>New &#8211; Meet the MonsterInsights Team!</h3>\n<p>With MonsterInsights 7.6, we’ve also added a new About page to our plugin menu. The MonsterInsights team is growing fast, and we wanted to take this opportunity to show off the work of the each individual on our team and connect more with our users.</p>\n<p>You can see our developers, writers, and support team on the MonsterInsights About page and learn all the insider behind-the-scenes info on MonsterInsights.</p>\n<p>After updating to the latest version, you can check it out at <strong>Insights &raquo; About Us</strong>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/about-the-monsterinsights-team-min.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"560\" height=\"247\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-199036\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/about-the-monsterinsights-team-min.png 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/about-the-monsterinsights-team-min-300x132.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>Leave a comment here or <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/contact/\">reach out</a> and let us know what you think!</p>\n<p>That’s it for today! We have plenty more amazing features planned for you, so stay tuned for upcoming announcements. Be sure to subscribe to our newsletter and follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook</a> to be the first to know.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/announcing-scroll-tracking-front-end-page-insights-and-more/\">Announcing Scroll Tracking, Front-End Page Insights, and More</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:97:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/announcing-scroll-tracking-front-end-page-insights-and-more/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"How to Create a Membership Website That Makes Money (2019)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:145:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-membership-website/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-create-a-membership-website\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-membership-website/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sun, 28 Apr 2019 19:32:41 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/?p=198572\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:601:\"<p>Do you want to create a membership website that makes money? Membership websites let you add content behind a locked gate so you can earn money by making people pay for access. Basically, they require people to buy a membership to view the gated content. Creating a membership site is a very popular online business [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-membership-website/\">How to Create a Membership Website That Makes Money (2019)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Sunita Rai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25264:\"<p>Do you want to create a membership website that makes money? Membership websites let you add content behind a locked gate so you can earn money by making people pay for access. Basically, they require people to buy a membership to view the gated content.</p>\n<p>Creating a membership site is a very popular online business model nowadays, and for good reason. Paid online courses, premium support forums, and webinars are among most profitable sites on the internet.</p>\n<p>In this article, we’ll show you how to easily create a membership website step-by-step. Let’s get started with the table of contents:</p>\n<p><strong>Table of Contents</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"#choosesiteplatform\">Choosing the right platform for your membership website</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#setupwpmembershipsite\">Setting up your WordPress membership site</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#setupmemberpress\">Setting up your membership plugin</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#payment\">Adding payment methods</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#memebrshiplevels\">Adding membership levels</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#accessrules\">Setting up access rules for your membership plans</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#createcontent\">Creating members-only content</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#pricingpage\">Creating a pricing page</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#signuplogin\">Adding sign up and login forms</a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Now, we’ll walk you through these steps one-by-one.</p>\n<h3 id=\"choosesiteplatform\">Step 1: Choosing the Right Platform for Your Membership Site</h3>\n<p>The first step to making a membership website is to choose the right website platform. While there’re many generic website builders on the market, you&#8217;ll need a platform that specifically fulfills the needs of a membership site.</p>\n<p>Some of the most important features you’ll need for your membership website are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Membership Management – option to create different types of memberships, and to add and manage members.</li>\n<li>User Registration and Member Profiles – frontend options for your users to sign up or login to your site, and to access their member profiles.</li>\n<li>Content Restriction – options to hide your content from general audiences.</li>\n<li>Payment Options – options to integrate payment gateways to accept online payments.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You can add these features in almost any platform; however, most will require technical skills. If you don’t have any coding skills, you may need to hire a developer.</p>\n<p>Luckily, WordPress comes with an easy way to build membership websites. By using powerful WordPress membership plugins, you can quickly set up a membership website and start selling with little-to-no technical skills.</p>\n<p>There’re many free and premium membership plugins, so you may get confused trying to figure out which one to use. Check out our detailed comparison post on the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-wordpress-membership-plugins-compared/\">best WordPress membership plugins</a> to make your selection more easily.</p>\n<p>In this article, we’ll use the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/memberpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">MemberPress</a> plugin to create a membership website. It’s the most popular WordPress membership plugin in the world.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/memberpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-194244\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberspresswordpressmembershipplugin.png\" alt=\"MemberPress Best WordPress Membership Plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberspresswordpressmembershipplugin.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberspresswordpressmembershipplugin-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>MemberPress comes with advanced features that let you create multiple membership levels, restrict access to content, accept payments, and more. Also, it integrates well with email marketing services and other useful tools like bbPress and Affiliate Royale.</p>\n<p>With that said, let’s start setting up your WordPress membership website.</p>\n<h3 id=\"setupwpmembershipsite\">Step 2: Setting Up Your WordPress Membership Site</h3>\n<p>In addition to a membership plugin, you’ll need a domain a name, a web hosting account, and an SSL certificate to create a membership site with WordPress.</p>\n<p>A domain name is the web address of your membership site — for example, monsterinsights.com or google.com. A web hosting account is where your website files are stored online. And, an SSL certificate is required to make secure transactions.</p>\n<p>You can buy a domain name for around $14.99 per year, web hosting for $7.99 per month, and an SSL certificate for $49.99 per year.</p>\n<p>If you add these amounts together, the total cost would be very high, especially if you&#8217;re a beginner without a big budget.</p>\n<p>Fortunately, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Bluehost</a> is offering an exclusive deal to our customers. Now you can enjoy 60% off on WordPress hosting, get a free domain, and nab a free SSL certificate along with it. That means you can get all 3 of these essentials for just $2.75 per month.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-185172\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/bluehostwordpresshosting.jpg\" alt=\"Bluehost Best WordPress Hosting\" width=\"620\" height=\"375\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/bluehostwordpresshosting.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/bluehostwordpresshosting-300x181.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Bluehost is one of the oldest and most popular web hosting companies in the world. They’re officially recommended by both WordPress.org and the world&#8217;s most popular unofficial WordPress resource website, <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WPBeginner</a>.</p>\n<p>To get started, you need to choose a domain name and sign up for your hosting account. Once done, the next step is usually to <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/how-to-install-wordpress/ target=_blank\">install WordPress</a>; but you won’t need to do it manually because it comes pre-installed on your Bluehost account.</p>\n<p>Therefore, the next step is to install and configure your membership plugin. Let&#8217;s do that now.</p>\n<h3 id=\"setupmemberpress\">Step 3: Setting Up Your Membership Plugin</h3>\n<p>As mentioned above, we’ve chosen the MemberPress plugin for this tutorial.</p>\n<p>First, you&#8217;ll need to install and activate the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/memberpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">MemberPress</a> plugin. For detailed instructions, see our guide on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">how to install a WordPress plugin</a>.</p>\n<p>Once the plugin is activated, you’ll see a notification bar with a link to the plugin&#8217;s Options page for configuring.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198632\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/go-to-memberpress-options.png\" alt=\"Go to MemberPress Options Page\" width=\"620\" height=\"102\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/go-to-memberpress-options.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/go-to-memberpress-options-300x49.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Simply click on the ‘options page’ link, and it’ll take you to your MemberPress options page. Alternately, you can go to <strong>MemberPress » Options</strong> to access the plugin&#8217;s settings.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198633\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberpressoptions.png\" alt=\"MemberPress Options Page\" width=\"620\" height=\"449\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberpressoptions.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberpressoptions-300x217.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>From this page, you can configure all your plugin settings.</p>\n<h3 id=\"payment\">Step 4: Adding Payment Methods</h3>\n<p>Payments are of vital importance. Click on the ‘Payments’ tab in the Options page to configure the payment gateways for your membership website.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198634\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberpresspaymentoptions.png\" alt=\"MemberPress Payment Options\" width=\"620\" height=\"290\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberpresspaymentoptions.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberpresspaymentoptions-300x140.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>MemberPress, by default, allows you to use PayPal (Standard and Express), Stripe, and Authorize.net as your payment gateway. You can configure one or multiple gateways for your website.</p>\n<h3 id=\"memebrshiplevels\">Step 5: Adding Membership Levels</h3>\n<p>Once you’ve configured the settings, the next step is to add membership levels that people can purchase. MemberPress allows you to create unlimited membership levels, each with different pricing, features, and content access.</p>\n<p>Go to <strong>MemberPress » Memberhips</strong> from your dashboard menu and click the ‘Add New’ button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198635\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addnewmembership.png\" alt=\"Add New Membership with MemberPress\" width=\"620\" height=\"237\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addnewmembership.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addnewmembership-300x115.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>On the next screen, you’ll see a page that looks similar to the Classic WordPress editor. On this page, you can create a membership level.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198636\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addmembershipcontent.png\" alt=\"Add Membership Content in WordPress\" width=\"620\" height=\"322\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addmembershipcontent.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addmembershipcontent-300x156.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Enter a title and add a description for your membership level in the editor. Next, set the price, choose a billing type, and set an access time or expiry date from the ‘Membership Terms’ section on the right side of the page.</p>\n<p>After that, scroll down to the ‘Membership Options’ section to configure the registration, permissions, price box, and more.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198637\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/membershipoptions.png\" alt=\"Membership Options for registration and more\" width=\"620\" height=\"287\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/membershipoptions.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/membershipoptions-300x139.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you’ve configured all the settings, go ahead and publish your membership level.</p>\n<h3 id=\"accessrules\">Step 6: Setting Up Access Rules for Your Membership Plans</h3>\n<p>Now that you’ve created membership levels, the next step is to set up rules to define which content can be accessed for those different membership levels.</p>\n<p>Navigate to <strong>MemberPress » Rules</strong> and click on the ‘Add New’ button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198638\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addnewmemberspressrule.png\" alt=\"Add New Membership Rule\" width=\"620\" height=\"279\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addnewmemberspressrule.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addnewmemberspressrule-300x135.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>On the next screen, you can create a new rule to link your content to the membership levels.</p>\n<p>For example, you can select all the content under a particular category to be accessible by users with a specific subscription plan.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198639\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/setupnewmembershiprule.png\" alt=\"Set Up Membership Rule in WordPress\" width=\"620\" height=\"427\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/setupnewmembershiprule.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/setupnewmembershiprule-300x207.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>In the screenshot above, we’ve selected all the content in the ‘Advanced WordPress Guide’ category to be available only to members with a Platinum or Gold subscription plan.</p>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll see the ‘Drip/Expiration’ box. Enabling the drip option will allow you to gradually release content; whereas the expiration option will let you choose the time in which the content will no longer be available.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198640\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dripandexpirationoptionsmemberpress.png\" alt=\"Drip and Expiration Options in MemberPress\" width=\"620\" height=\"205\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dripandexpirationoptionsmemberpress.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dripandexpirationoptionsmemberpress-300x99.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you’ve configured all the options, save your rule. You can create more rules by repeating those same steps.</p>\n<h3 id=\"createcontent\">Step 7: Creating Members-Only Content</h3>\n<p>The next step is to create members-only content.</p>\n<p>Members-only content refers to the gated content which cannot be accessed by the general public and is available only to your registered members.</p>\n<p>You can add content with posts or pages, just like you would on a typical WordPress website. Below, we’ll create a post with the ‘Advanced WordPress Guide’ category to match the rule we created in the last step.</p>\n<p>Simply create a new post and add content to it. Then, select the ‘Advanced WordPress Guide’ category.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198641\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addcontentandchoosecategory.png\" alt=\"Add Content to a Post and Choose a Category \" width=\"620\" height=\"368\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addcontentandchoosecategory.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addcontentandchoosecategory-300x178.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>After that, scroll down to the ‘MemberPress Unauthorized Access’ section. You can set up what non-members (non-registered users) will see when they try to access this content.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198642\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/unauthorizedaccessoptionsonpost.png\" alt=\"Unauthorized Access Option in a WordPress Post\" width=\"620\" height=\"341\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/unauthorizedaccessoptionsonpost.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/unauthorizedaccessoptionsonpost-300x165.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you’ve added your content and configured everything, you can publish your page. After that, you can visit <strong>Posts » All Posts</strong> and see which content is protected for certain membership holders.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198643\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/members-onlycontentmemberpress.png\" alt=\"Members-only Content in WordPress\" width=\"620\" height=\"205\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/members-onlycontentmemberpress.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/members-onlycontentmemberpress-300x99.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3 id=\"pricingpage\">Step 8: Creating a Pricing Page</h3>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll need to create a pricing page where your site visitors can choose a membership plan and sign up for that plan. The MemberPress plugin lets you create a pricing page easily using its Group options.</p>\n<p>Visit <strong>MemberPress » Groups</strong> from your admin panel and click on the ‘Add New’ button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198644\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addnewgroupforpricingpage.png\" alt=\"Add New Group for Pricing Page\" width=\"620\" height=\"290\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addnewgroupforpricingpage.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addnewgroupforpricingpage-300x140.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Enter your group title first. You can name it ‘Pricing Plans’ or something similar because it’ll ultimately serve as your pricing page.</p>\n<p>Next, scroll down to the ‘Group Options’ section and add the memberships you want to show on your pricing page. Also choose your pricing page&#8217;s theme.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198645\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberpressgroupoptions.png\" alt=\"MemberPress Group Options\" width=\"620\" height=\"451\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberpressgroupoptions.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberpressgroupoptions-300x218.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve configured all the options, click the ‘Publish’ button.</p>\n<p>If you want to see how your pricing page looks, you can preview it. Here’s how a MemberPress pricing page will appear on the default Twenty Nineteen theme:</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198646\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/pricingpagedemo.png\" alt=\"MemberPress Pricing Page Demo in Twenty Nineteen theme\" width=\"620\" height=\"344\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/pricingpagedemo.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/pricingpagedemo-300x166.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>After that, you&#8217;ll need to direct unauthorized users (non-members) to the pricing page.</p>\n<p>Visit <strong>MemberPress » Groups</strong> page and copy the URL of the group you created before.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198647\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/copygroupurlmemberpress.png\" alt=\"Copy the group URL to redirect non-members to Pricing Page\" width=\"620\" height=\"205\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/copygroupurlmemberpress.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/copygroupurlmemberpress-300x99.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, go to the <strong>MemberPress » Options</strong> page and go down to the ‘Unauthorized Access’ section.</p>\n<p>Now, check the box next to ‘Redirect unauthorized visitors to a specific URL’ and then paste the group URL you copied earlier.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198648\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/redirectunauthorizedvisitorstopricingpage.png\" alt=\"Redirect unauthorized users to Pricing Page\" width=\"620\" height=\"355\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/redirectunauthorizedvisitorstopricingpage.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/redirectunauthorizedvisitorstopricingpage-300x172.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>After that, click on the ‘Update Options’ button at the bottom. Now your non-members and unauthorized visitors will be redirected to your pricing page whenever they try to access your hidden premium content.</p>\n<h3 id=\"signuplogin\">Step 9: Adding Sign Up and Login Forms</h3>\n<p>Now you’ve set up everything, the final step is to add sign up and login forms to your site. The MemberPress plugin lets you make a website with user accounts and profiles with ease.</p>\n<p>First, you can add a user login form using a widget. Go to <strong>Appearance » Widegts</strong> from your admin panel and add the ‘MemberPress Login’ widget to a widget-ready area.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198649\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addmembershiploginwidgettoyoursite.png\" alt=\"Add MemberPress Login widget to Your website\" width=\"620\" height=\"252\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addmembershiploginwidgettoyoursite.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addmembershiploginwidgettoyoursite-300x122.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll need to add your pricing page URL to your navigation menu so your website visitors can sign up for a membership plan.</p>\n<p>Visit <strong>Appearance » Menus</strong> page from your dashboard. Create a new menu or choose an existing menu. Next, select ‘Pricing Plans’ under the ‘Groups’ tab and then click on the ‘Add to Menu’ button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198650\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addpricingplanspagetowpmenu.jpg\" alt=\"Add Pricing Page to WordPress Menu\" width=\"620\" height=\"501\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addpricingplanspagetowpmenu.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addpricingplanspagetowpmenu-300x242.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Once your pricing page appears below the menu structure, you can drag it to rearrange its position. Once satisfied, don’t forget to save your menu.</p>\n<p>That’s it! Now you can open your website and preview it in action.</p>\n<h3>Optimizing Your WordPress Membership Website for Growth</h3>\n<p>Now that you’ve created a WordPress membership website, your next task is to optimize it for more traffic and more transactions. Luckily, there’re plenty of plugins and tools to help you out.</p>\n<p>You can use the following plugins and tools to grow your membership website:</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">1. MonsterInsights</a></strong>: The best Google Analytics plugin for WordPress. You can use this plugin to get complete insights into your users and eCommerce transactions.</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ target=\">2. OptinMonster</a></strong>: The best lead generation software on the market. It helps you build your email list faster and increase your website conversions.</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.wpforms.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">3. WPForms</a></strong>: The absolute best WordPress form builder plugin available. You can use this plugin to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-contact-form-in-wordpress-the-simple-way/\">create a simple contact form</a> as well as interactive <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-survey-in-wordpress/&quot;\">surveys</a> and conversational forms, like Typeform.</p>\n<p>If you want to add more features to your website, check out our complete list of <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/must-have-wordpress-plugins-and-tools-for-business-websites/\">must-have WordPress plugins and tools for business websites</a>.</p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you create a fully functional membership website that earns money. You may also want to read our guide on <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-free-business-email-address/\">how to create a free business email address</a>.</p>\n<p>And don’t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more helpful Google Analytics tips.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-membership-website/\">How to Create a Membership Website That Makes Money (2019)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-membership-website/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"How to Add Affiliate Links in WordPress (and Properly Track Them)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:203:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-affiliate-links-in-wordpress-and-properly-track-them/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-add-affiliate-links-in-wordpress-and-properly-track-them\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:104:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-affiliate-links-in-wordpress-and-properly-track-them/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 25 Apr 2019 13:15:52 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23:\"affiliate link tracking\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"affiliate marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35:\"adding affiliate links in WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/?p=155556\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:645:\"<p>Wondering how to add affiliate links in WordPress? If you&#8217;ve got a blog with a decent number of daily visitors, you can earn plenty of referral income with affiliate marketing; but you have to be smart when choosing the tools to turn your blog into a successful affiliate marketing site. In this article, we’ll show [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-affiliate-links-in-wordpress-and-properly-track-them/\">How to Add Affiliate Links in WordPress (and Properly Track Them)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Sunita Rai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16053:\"<p>Wondering how to add affiliate links in WordPress? If you&#8217;ve got a blog with a decent number of daily visitors, you can earn plenty of referral income with affiliate marketing; but you have to be smart when choosing the tools to turn your blog into a successful affiliate marketing site.</p>\n<p>In this article, we’ll show you how to add and organize affiliate links in WordPress using ThirstyAffiliates. Then, in the last section of the article, we’ll show how to properly track your affiliate links to grow your affiliate marketing.</p>\n<h3>Using ThirstyAffiliates to Add and Organize Affiliate Links in WordPress</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/thirstyaffiliates/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">ThirstyAffiliates</a> is the best affiliate management and cloaking plugin for WordPress. It helps you to cloak your affiliate links and add them into your blog posts with ease. You can also organize your affiliate links by categories and add automatic keywords so that affiliate management in WordPress will be really easy.</p>\n<p>In general, affiliate links are long and look ugly that are hard to remember. Most affiliate links look like this:</p>\n<p>http://example.com/products/?product_id=123&#038;affiliate_id</p>\n<p>ThirstyAffiliates helps you to cloak such affiliate links to make them short and branded URLs as shown below:</p>\n<p>http://www.yoursite.com/recommends/productname</p>\n<p>As you grow as an affiliate marketer, you’re likely to use the same affiliate link on tons of different blog posts. With ThirstyAffiliates, you can store all your affiliate links in one place in your WordPress backend and use them whenever you need. Plus, it has a fully functional search option to help you search for links by the link title.</p>\n<p>In addition to proper management of affiliate links, cloaking also helps you to prevent commission theft. By using cloaked links, you can add an additional layer of click tracking to ensure you are getting paid for every sale you refer.</p>\n<p>Now, let’s go ahead and see how to add affiliate links in WordPress step-by-step.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Install ThirstyAffiliates and Configure Settings</h3>\n<p>First of all, go to the <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/thirstyaffiliates/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">ThirstyAffiliates</a> website and buy a subscription plan. Then, go ahead and install the plugin in WordPress.</p>\n<p>After the plugin is activated on your site, go to <strong>ThirstyAffiliates » Settings</strong> from your WordPress dashboard. This will open the <strong>General</strong> tab in ThirstyAffiliate Settings.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155953\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-general-settings.jpg\" alt=\"thirstyaffiliates-general-settings\" width=\"560\" height=\"290\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-general-settings.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-general-settings-300x155.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>Now, you can review all the settings and change the settings if you want to. At the end, don’t forget to click the <strong>Save Changes</strong> button.</p>\n<p>Second tab in ThirstyAffiliates settings is <strong>Link Appearance</strong>. It allows you to configure settings that affect the behavior and appearance or your affiliate links. You can configure some of the important settings from there.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155954\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-link-appearance-settings.jpg\" alt=\"thirstyaffiliates-link-appearance-settings\" width=\"560\" height=\"312\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-link-appearance-settings.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-link-appearance-settings-300x167.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>First, you can choose a link prefix that will be used in your cloaked links before your affiliate ID. The plugin, by default, has <strong>/recommends/</strong> set up which you can replace with any of the available prefixes such as recommends, fly, proceed, goto, etc. Also, you can choose <strong>custom</strong> to add a new prefix.</p>\n<p>Next, you can choose whether you want to show a link category in your affiliate URL or not. Then, you can choose link redirect type, use no follow on links, and open links in new window.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155955\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-link-appearance-settings-2.jpg\" alt=\"thirstyaffiliates-link-appearance-settings-2\" width=\"560\" height=\"510\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-link-appearance-settings-2.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-link-appearance-settings-2-300x273.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>Review all the settings, make the necessary changes, and then, click <strong>Save Changes</strong> button.</p>\n<p>The third tab in ThirstAffiliates Settings is <strong>Modules</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155956\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-module-settings.jpg\" alt=\"thirstyaffiliates-module-settings\" width=\"560\" height=\"422\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-module-settings.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-module-settings-300x226.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>From this page, you can enable ThirstyAffiliates statistics that collects data about your users who click your affiliate links. If it&#8217;s enabled, it shows reports; however, the module slows down your site. So we recommend using <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights</a> for tracking your affiliate links.</p>\n<p>The <strong>Link Fixer</strong> will help you to fix any outdated / broken affiliate links on your site. <strong>Uncloak Links</strong> will allow you to uncloak specific links or categories to make it compatible with some affiliate programs with stricter terms (such as Amazon Associates).</p>\n<p>The fourth tab <strong>Import/Export</strong> provides you with options to export ThirstyAffiliates settings and import settings from other WordPress sites.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155957\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-import-export-settings.jpg\" alt=\"thirstyaffiliates-import-export-settings\" width=\"560\" height=\"450\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-import-export-settings.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-import-export-settings-300x241.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>After you choose the options, make sure to click the <strong>Save Changes</strong> button.</p>\n<h3>Step 2: Add Link Categories and New Affiliate Links</h3>\n<p>After you’ve configured the settings, you’re now ready to create link categories.</p>\n<p>To add link categories, go to <strong>ThirstyAffiliates » Link Categories</strong> from your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155958\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-link-categories.jpg\" alt=\"thirstyaffiliates-link-categories\" width=\"560\" height=\"379\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-link-categories.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-link-categories-300x203.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>Now, give a name to your new link category, set a slug, and add a description. Then, click the <strong>Add New Category</strong> button.</p>\n<p>After you create sufficient categories for your links, you can go ahead and add your links.</p>\n<p>To add a new affiliate link, you’ll need to go to <strong>ThirstyAffiliates » New Affiliate Link</strong> from your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n<p>Now, you can easily add affiliate links.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155959\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/add-affiliate-link-thirstyaffiliates.jpg\" alt=\"add-affiliate-link-thirstyaffiliates\" width=\"560\" height=\"325\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/add-affiliate-link-thirstyaffiliates.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/add-affiliate-link-thirstyaffiliates-300x174.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>In the first field, give a name to your link. You can use the product’s name so that it’ll be easy to search and embed in posts.</p>\n<p>Next, you’ll need to add the original affiliate link in the <strong>Destination URL</strong> field.</p>\n<p>Then, you can attach images as well. This is useful for website owners who want to display affiliate links with images in sidebars. You can also add autolink keywords for your affiliate link if you’re using ThirstyAffiliates&#8217; paid version.</p>\n<p>In the right panel, you can choose a link category. As you scroll down, you can find link options. You’ll see the options as you configured in the <strong>Link Appearance</strong> as we discussed above. Review them, and click the <strong>Save Link</strong> button.</p>\n<p>That’s it. Now, you can repeat the same process to add more affiliate links.</p>\n<h3>Step 3: Adding Affiliate Links in WordPress Posts and Pages</h3>\n<p>Once you’ve added affiliate links in <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/thirstyaffiliates/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">ThirstyAffiliates</a>, now you can add the cloaked affiliate links in your posts and pages.</p>\n<p>ThirstyAffiliates makes the process of adding links really easy as it adds an icon in your post editor to embed affiliate links.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155960\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/embed-affiliate-link-in-post.jpg\" alt=\"embed-affiliate-link-in-post\" width=\"560\" height=\"261\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/embed-affiliate-link-in-post.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/embed-affiliate-link-in-post-300x140.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>As you click on the link, it’ll open the search box where you can type your affiliate link name. Then, you can select and add on your post.</p>\n<p>It also has another icon, <strong>Quick Add Affiliate Link</strong>, that you can use to add a new affiliate link and embed it in your post.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155961\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/quck-add-affiliate-link-icon.jpg\" alt=\"quck-add-affiliate-link-icon\" width=\"560\" height=\"195\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/quck-add-affiliate-link-icon.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/quck-add-affiliate-link-icon-300x104.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>When you click on the icon, a popup box will appear. You can add a new affiliate link and then embed it in the post.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155962\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/quck-add-affiliate-link-thirstyaffiliates.jpg\" alt=\"quck-add-affiliate-link-thirstyaffiliates\" width=\"560\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/quck-add-affiliate-link-thirstyaffiliates.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/quck-add-affiliate-link-thirstyaffiliates-300x161.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>That’s it. Now, you can publish your post and check if your affiliate links are working.</p>\n<h3>How to Properly Track Your Affiliate Links</h3>\n<p>ThirstyAffilites comes with a Statistics module that tracks the affiliate clicks on your site; however, it’ll slow down your website because it uses your website&#8217;s resources.</p>\n<p>So, we recommend you use <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights</a> to track your affiliate links. Since it uses event-based tracking from Google Analytics, it won’t affect your website speed. Plus, the reports from Google Analytics are more reliable than any other services.</p>\n<p>Now, let’s see how to enable affiliate tracking in WordPress using MonsterInsights.</p>\n<h3>Affiliate Links Tracking with MonsterInsights</h3>\n<p>MonsterInsights makes affiliate links tracking for ThirstAffiliates fully automatic and effortless. Now you don&#8217;t need to do a single thing to set up affiliate tracking in WordPress. </p>\n<p>When the MonsterInsights plugin is installed on your site, it&#8217;ll automatically detect if you&#8217;re using ThirstyAffiliates and track all your affiliate links. Use any prefix (/refer/, /recommends/ or /out/), the plugin will do its job. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/affiliate-link-tracking.png\" alt=\"Affiliate Link Tracking with MonsterInsights\" width=\"620\" height=\"292\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-179067\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/affiliate-link-tracking.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/affiliate-link-tracking-300x141.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>The automatic affiliate tracking feature empowers anyone to manage affiliate tracking without having to hire a developer. Also, you can save plenty of time and reduce all the possible setup errors.  </p>\n<p>Best of all, you can view your affiliate tracking reports right in your WordPress dashboard. Just visit <strong> Insights » Reports » Publishers</strong> from your admin panel to view the reports.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155898\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/affiliate-link-tracking-report-monsterinsights.jpg\" alt=\"affiliate-link-tracking-report-monsterinsights\" width=\"560\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/affiliate-link-tracking-report-monsterinsights.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/affiliate-link-tracking-report-monsterinsights-280x300.jpg 280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>You can always click the <strong>View All Affiliate Links Report</strong> to view more reports in Google Analytics.</p>\n<p>If you want detailed instructions, here’s our complete guide on <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-set-up-affiliate-link-tracking-in-wordpress/\">setting up affiliate links tracking</a>.</p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you to learn how to add affiliate links in WordPress and to properly track them.</p>\n<p>You might also want to check out our guide on <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-check-the-number-of-visitors-for-your-wordpress-site/\">how to check the number of visitors for your WordPress site</a>.</p>\n<p>Also, don’t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more Google Analytics tutorials.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-affiliate-links-in-wordpress-and-properly-track-them/\">How to Add Affiliate Links in WordPress (and Properly Track Them)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:101:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-affiliate-links-in-wordpress-and-properly-track-them/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:60:\"The Beginners Guide to Custom Dimensions in Google Analytics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:197:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/the-beginners-guide-to-custom-dimensions-in-google-analytics/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=the-beginners-guide-to-custom-dimensions-in-google-analytics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:102:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/the-beginners-guide-to-custom-dimensions-in-google-analytics/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 22 Apr 2019 12:00:47 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"Google Analytics\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"custom dimensions\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"custom dimensions tracking\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/?p=103958\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:676:\"<p>Want to track your own custom data in Google Analytics? With custom dimensions, you can set your own custom tracking parameters and display it in your MonsterInsights dashboard and Google Analytics report. In this article, we’ll explain everything you need to know about custom dimensions. What Are Custom Dimensions? Every Google Analytics report contains two [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/the-beginners-guide-to-custom-dimensions-in-google-analytics/\">The Beginners Guide to Custom Dimensions in Google Analytics</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:13:\"Shahzad Saeed\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28308:\"<p>Want to track your own custom data in Google Analytics? With custom dimensions, you can set your own custom tracking parameters and display it in your MonsterInsights dashboard and Google Analytics report. In this article, we’ll explain everything you need to know about custom dimensions.</p>\n<h3>What Are Custom Dimensions?</h3>\n<p>Every Google Analytics report contains two types of data: dimensions and metrics.</p>\n<p>Dimensions are attributes of your website visitors and metrics are quantitative measurements of dimensions. In a tabular Google Analytics report, dimensions are shown in rows and metrics in the columns.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dimensionandmetricsinga.png\" alt=\"Dimension and Metrics in Google Analytics Report\" width=\"620\" height=\"365\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-196886\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dimensionandmetricsinga.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/dimensionandmetricsinga-300x177.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>In the screenshot above, the &#8216;country&#8217; is the dimension and the data for each country like the number of users, sessions, bounce rate, revenue, etc. are the metrics. </p>\n<p>Google Analytics tracks certain dimensions and metrics by default. Gender, age, region, source/medium, product, goals, etc. are some <strong>predefined dimensions</strong> whereas pageview, bounce rate, average time on a page are some <strong>predefined metrics</strong>. </p>\n<p>But what if you want to track more dimensions? </p>\n<p>That&#8217;s when the custom dimensions option comes handy. Google Analytics allows you to add and track new dimensions easily.  </p>\n<p>Custom dimensions are just like default dimensions, except you create them yourself. They&#8217;re greatly helpful to collect and analyze data that matter to your website, which Analytics doesn&#8217;t automatically track.</p>\n<p>The main benefit of setting up custom dimension is that it allows you to track the performance of every important element (or dimension) that matters to your website like Author, Category, Tags, etc. in Google Analytics.</p>\n<p>With MonsterInsights, you can easily set up the following custom dimensions.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Logged in</li>\n<li>User Id</li>\n<li>Post Type</li>\n<li>Author</li>\n<li>Category</li>\n<li>Published at</li>\n<li>Tags</li>\n<li>SEO Score</li>\n<li>Focus Keyword</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>How to Use Custom Dimensions &#8211; Some Use Cases</h3>\n<p>Now let’s take a look at a few possible use cases of custom dimensions in your WordPress website.</p>\n<p><strong>Author</strong></p>\n<p>If you’re running a multi-author blog, author tracking gives you valuable insights on the performance of your blog authors.</p>\n<p>You can discover,</p>\n<ul>\n<li>the most popular author of your blog</li>\n<li>how many pageviews each author is getting</li>\n<li>which author’s posts keep visitors on your site by <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-find-your-bounce-rate-in-google-analytics/\">analyzing the bounce rate</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Logged in</strong></p>\n<p>Let’s say that you’re an eCommerce store owner who wants to better track the interaction of logged in users. Since logged in users are those who matter the most to your eCommerce business, setting up a custom dimension for logged in users will give you more insights about them that you may have otherwise missed.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You can track the most popular products amongst your logged in users by gender. This data can help you to personalize the shopping experience of your customers.</li>\n<li>You can get a detailed report of every logged in users like their purchasing behavior, what product category they’re interested in and more.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Others</strong></p>\n<p>Custom dimensions give you endless possibilities to track important elements that matter to your website and online business.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You can add <strong>Post Type</strong> tracking to see which one of your WordPress post types perform better.</li>\n<li>You can add <strong>Category</strong> tracking to see which sections of your sites are the most popular.</li>\n<li>You can add <strong>SEO Score</strong> tracking to see which blog posts are the most popular.</li>\n<li>You can add <strong>Focus Keyword</strong> tracking to see which of your content is doing well in search engines.</li>\n<li>and more…</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>How to Set Up Custom Dimensions Tracking in 2 Minutes</h3>\n<p>You need to set up custom dimensions both in your WordPress website and Google Analytics account. Let’s walk through the whole setup process step by step.</p>\n<p><strong>Step 1: Install MonsterInsights and Custom Dimensions</strong></p>\n<p>Without MonsterInsights, setting up custom dimensions on your site can be tricky and time-consuming especially when you’re not tech savvy. MonsterInsights makes it easy to set up custom dimensions on your WordPress site in just a few clicks, without having to touch a single line of code.</p>\n<p>To be able to set up custom dimensions on your site, you’ll require the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/pricing\">MonsterInsights</a> plugin and the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/dimensions/\">Custom Dimensions addon</a> (available to Pro level users and above).</p>\n<p>First off, install MonsterInsights on your site and <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-properly-setup-google-analytics-in-wordpress/\">properly authenticate it with Google Analytics</a>.</p>\n<p>Next, you’ll want to install the Custom Dimensions addon.</p>\n<p>To install the addon, visit the <strong>Insights » Addons</strong> page in your WordPress dashboard. Then, click <strong>Install</strong> under the MonsterInsights Custom Dimensions addon.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-89812\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/install-dimensions-addon.jpg\" alt=\"install custom dimensions addon\" width=\"540\" height=\"237\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/install-dimensions-addon.jpg 540w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/install-dimensions-addon-300x132.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" /></p>\n<p>After installation is complete, the button will change to say <strong>Activate</strong>. Go ahead and click the <strong>Activate</strong> button to make sure the addon is active and ready to use.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-89835\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/activateaddon.png\" alt=\"activate the custom dimensions addon\" width=\"540\" height=\"571\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/activateaddon.png 540w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/activateaddon-284x300.png 284w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Step 2: Add Custom Dimensions in MonsterInsights</strong></p>\n<p>Navigate to <strong>Insights &raquo; Settings</strong> from your dashboard and click on the <strong>Conversions</strong> tab. Scroll down to the <strong>Custom Dimensions</strong> section.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-176361\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/conversion-settings-custom-dimension-monsterinsights-e1545426201408.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1074\" height=\"729\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/conversion-settings-custom-dimension-monsterinsights-e1545426201408.jpg 1074w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/conversion-settings-custom-dimension-monsterinsights-e1545426201408-300x204.jpg 300w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/conversion-settings-custom-dimension-monsterinsights-e1545426201408-768x521.jpg 768w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/conversion-settings-custom-dimension-monsterinsights-e1545426201408-1024x695.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1074px) 100vw, 1074px\" /></p>\n<p>Now click on <strong>Add new custom dimension</strong>. You can choose from many dimensions. Once you are done selecting, click the <strong>Save Changes</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-176360\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/add-a-custom-dimension-monsterinsights-e1545425799584.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1074\" height=\"826\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/add-a-custom-dimension-monsterinsights-e1545425799584.jpg 1074w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/add-a-custom-dimension-monsterinsights-e1545425799584-300x231.jpg 300w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/add-a-custom-dimension-monsterinsights-e1545425799584-768x591.jpg 768w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/add-a-custom-dimension-monsterinsights-e1545425799584-1024x788.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1074px) 100vw, 1074px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Step 3: Set Up Custom Dimensions in Google Analytics</strong></p>\n<p>Now that you’ve set up Custom Dimensions on your website, the next step is to set them up in Google Analytics as well.</p>\n<p>To get started, you can log into <a href=\"http://www.google.com/analytics/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Google Analytics</a>, and select the website in which you&#8217;d like to set up custom dimensions.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-89613\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/google-analytics-property.jpg\" alt=\"click on google analytics view\" width=\"420\" height=\"239\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/google-analytics-property.jpg 420w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/google-analytics-property-300x171.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px\" /></p>\n<p>This will send you to the reporting part of Google Analytics. However, since we need to set up Custom Dimensions, you’ll have to click on the <strong>Admin</strong> tab in the left panel.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-98965\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/admin.jpg\" alt=\"click admin\" width=\"255\" height=\"281\" /></p>\n<p>On the Admin page, click <strong>Custom Definitions</strong> and then <strong>Custom Dimensions</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-84895\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/click-custom-dimensions.jpg\" alt=\"Click Custom Definitions, and then Custom Dimensions\" width=\"540\" height=\"335\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/click-custom-dimensions.jpg 540w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/click-custom-dimensions-300x186.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" /></p>\n<p>You’ll see a table where you can click <strong>+ New Custom Dimension</strong>. Click on it.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-84913\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/new-custom-dimension.png\" alt=\"click new custom dimension button\" width=\"446\" height=\"92\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/new-custom-dimension.png 446w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/new-custom-dimension-300x62.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 446px) 100vw, 446px\" /></p>\n<p>Now you can fill in the name of your new Custom Dimension and click <strong>Create</strong>. You don’t have to change any of the other settings.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-84921\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/create-custom-dimension.png\" alt=\"creating new custom dimension\" width=\"310\" height=\"324\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/create-custom-dimension.png 310w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/create-custom-dimension-287x300.png 287w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 310px) 100vw, 310px\" /></p>\n<p>On the next screen, you can just click <strong>Done</strong>.</p>\n<p>Repeat the steps above for all custom dimensions you want to add to your website.</p>\n<p><strong>Step 4: Match Custom Dimension IDs</strong></p>\n<p>The final step is to check that the index number in Google Analytics corresponds with the Custom Dimension ID in the MonsterInsights settings.</p>\n<p>First, check the index number for your custom dimensions in Google Analytics.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-85018\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/ga-custom-dimension-index.jpg\" alt=\"Google Analytics custom dimensions index number\" width=\"540\" height=\"160\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/ga-custom-dimension-index.jpg 540w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/ga-custom-dimension-index-300x89.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, go back to your Custom Dimensions settings in MonsterInsights. Make sure the Custom Dimension ID corresponds to the index number in Google Analytics. If not, type in the correct number and click <strong>Save Changes</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-176362\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/match-custom-dimensions.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"1080\" height=\"676\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/match-custom-dimensions.png 1080w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/match-custom-dimensions-300x188.png 300w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/match-custom-dimensions-768x481.png 768w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/match-custom-dimensions-1024x641.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px\" /></p>\n<h3>How to Find Custom Dimensions Report in Google Analytics</h3>\n<p>The best way to find the Custom Dimensions Report is by using <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/your-ultimate-guide-to-monsterinsights-dashboard-reports/\">MonsterInsights Dashboard reports</a>. You can view the most comprehensive reports right inside your WordPress dashboard, without having to open your Google Analytics account. </p>\n<p>You can view your custom dimensions reports in the MonsterInsights dashboard by going to <strong>Insights &raquo; Reports &raquo; Custom Dimensions</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-85148\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/custom-dimensions-report.jpg\" alt=\"viewing your MonsterInsights custom dimensions report\" width=\"540\" height=\"203\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/custom-dimensions-report.jpg 540w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/custom-dimensions-report-300x113.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" /></p>\n<p>Now you will see your Custom Dimensions reports in simple, beautiful charts. Here&#8217;s how your Authors Report would appear in MonsterInsights dashboard reports.  </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Most-Popular-Authors-Custom-Dimensions-Report-MonsterInsights-1.png\" alt=\"Most Popular Authors - Custom Dimensions Report - MonsterInsights\" width=\"1200\" height=\"1110\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-149539\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Most-Popular-Authors-Custom-Dimensions-Report-MonsterInsights-1.png 1200w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Most-Popular-Authors-Custom-Dimensions-Report-MonsterInsights-1-300x278.png 300w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Most-Popular-Authors-Custom-Dimensions-Report-MonsterInsights-1-768x710.png 768w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Most-Popular-Authors-Custom-Dimensions-Report-MonsterInsights-1-1024x947.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" /></p>\n<p>In Google Analytics, you can find custom dimensions report in two ways.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Using a standard report</li>\n<li>Creating a custom report</li>\n</ol>\n<p><strong>Using a Standard Report</strong></p>\n<p>This is probably the easiest way to find your custom dimensions report in Google Analytics. All you need to do is to add a secondary dimension to your standard report. We&#8217;ll walk you through how to do this below.</p>\n<p><strong>Creating a Custom Report</strong></p>\n<p>You can create a custom report by choosing a custom dimension as the primary dimension.  Creating a custom report is a great choice for you if…</p>\n<ul>\n<li>you want to label your custom dimension as the primary dimension.</li>\n<li>you want to add more than two dimensions (custom reports can have 5 dimensions) per row. The standard report allows you to use only two dimensions.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Let’s take a detailed look at how to find custom dimensions, step by step.</p>\n<h3>1. Find Custom Dimensions in a Standard Report</h3>\n<p>First off, you’ll need to <a href=\"https://analytics.google.com/analytics/web/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">log in to your Google Analytics account</a>, and select the website you’d like to find your Custom Dimensions report in.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-89613\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/google-analytics-property.jpg\" alt=\"click on google analytics view\" width=\"420\" height=\"239\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/google-analytics-property.jpg 420w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/google-analytics-property-300x171.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px\" /></p>\n<p>For the sake of this example, let’s add a custom dimension as a secondary dimension to your <strong>All Pages</strong> report.</p>\n<p>In the left panel, choose <strong>Behavior » Site Content » All Pages</strong>. Now you’ll see a standard All Pages report in Google Analytics.</p>\n<p>You can find a button labeled <strong>Secondary dimension</strong> just above the table. Click on it and choose your preferred custom dimension by clicking on the <strong>Custom Dimensions</strong> dropdown menu.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-103975\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/choose-a-custom-dimension-as-a-secondary-dimension.jpg\" alt=\"choose a secondary custom dimension\" width=\"550\" height=\"266\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/choose-a-custom-dimension-as-a-secondary-dimension.jpg 550w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/choose-a-custom-dimension-as-a-secondary-dimension-300x145.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\" /></p>\n<p>The report will look like this. See the below screenshot.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-103976\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/custom-dimension-report-in-Google-Analytics.jpg\" alt=\"custom dimension report Google Analytics\" width=\"550\" height=\"317\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/custom-dimension-report-in-Google-Analytics.jpg 550w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/05/custom-dimension-report-in-Google-Analytics-300x173.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\" /></p>\n<p>The same way, you can add a custom dimension as a secondary dimension to any other standard report.</p>\n<h3>2. Create a Custom Report for Custom Dimensions</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://analytics.google.com/analytics/web/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Log in to your Google Analytics account</a>, and select the website you’d like to find your Custom Dimension reports in.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-89613\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/google-analytics-property.jpg\" alt=\"click on google analytics view\" width=\"420\" height=\"239\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/google-analytics-property.jpg 420w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/google-analytics-property-300x171.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 420px) 100vw, 420px\" /></p>\n<p>Then, click the <strong>Customization / Customisation</strong> tab in the left panel.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-99059\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customization-tab.jpg\" alt=\"customization-tab\" width=\"246\" height=\"431\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customization-tab.jpg 246w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/customization-tab-171x300.jpg 171w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 246px) 100vw, 246px\" /></p>\n<p>You can now click the <strong>+ New Custom Report</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-89971\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/new-custom-report.png\" alt=\"create new custom report in google anlaytics\" width=\"540\" height=\"206\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/new-custom-report.png 540w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/new-custom-report-300x114.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" /></p>\n<p>Now you’ll need to tell Google Analytics what to include in your report.</p>\n<p>In this guide, we’ll create a report to show us the number of pageviews by author. We named our report <strong>Pageviews by Author.</strong></p>\n<p>Under Metric Groups, click the + add metric button. Type <strong>pageviews</strong>” in the search field. Then click on the<strong> Pageviews</strong> metric under the <strong>Users</strong> heading.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-89973\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/create-custom-report.png\" alt=\"creating a custom report in google analytics\" width=\"485\" height=\"601\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/create-custom-report.png 485w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/create-custom-report-242x300.png 242w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 485px) 100vw, 485px\" /></p>\n<p>After that, you can click the <strong>+ add dimension</strong> button and then click <strong>Custom Dimensions</strong> to specify the Custom Dimension you want to report.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-89974\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/custom-dimension-report.png\" alt=\"selecting the custom dimension for the report\" width=\"402\" height=\"329\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/custom-dimension-report.png 402w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/custom-dimension-report-300x246.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 402px) 100vw, 402px\" /></p>\n<p>When you’re done, click the <strong>Save</strong> button at the bottom.</p>\n<p>That’s it! Now you’ll be redirected to your new report.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-89976\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/pageviews-by-author-report.jpg\" alt=\"custom dimensions pageviews by author report\" width=\"540\" height=\"495\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/pageviews-by-author-report.jpg 540w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/04/pageviews-by-author-report-300x275.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" /></p>\n<p>Now you can access it at any time by navigating to <strong>Customization » Custom Reports » Pageviews by Author</strong>.</p>\n<h3>How to Use Custom Report Data to Grow Your Business</h3>\n<p>Custom dimensions report gives you detailed insights on the dimension you choose that you may have otherwise missed. You can make use of these data to improve the user experience, engagement, conversions and revenue of your online business.</p>\n<p>With MonsterInsights, you can set 8 types of custom dimensions. Below are a few tips to use the custom dimensions report in Google Analytics based on them.</p>\n<h3>1. Logged In</h3>\n<p>For example, if you&#8217;re an eCommerce shop owner, you can gather more insightful data about your logged in users to identify what works best for them. You can create custom reports by choosing your custom dimension as primary and two or more predefined dimensions (like gender, traffic source or other eCommerce data) as secondary. This way, you can personalize the shopping experience of your customers based on their gender and other dimensions.</p>\n<h3>2. User ID</h3>\n<p>You can get detailed insights about the visitor interaction, preferences of logged in users of a membership site by setting User ID as a custom dimension. This way, you can customize the user experience of your membership site.</p>\n<h3>3. Post Type</h3>\n<p>If you have several custom post types in your WordPress site, you can track the performance of each post type with custom dimensions.</p>\n<p>For example, imagine that you run a review site in which you review several categories of products. If you define each product category as a custom post type, you can track how users interact on each category and gather valuable data about it.</p>\n<h3>4. Author</h3>\n<p>If you run a multi-author blog, you can identify what works best for each author. It helps you to curate future blog post ideas for each author and restructure your content marketing strategy based on it.</p>\n<h3>5. Category</h3>\n<p>Tracking the performance of different categories of your site is another great strategy to identify what works best. This data can be helpful to save your time and money.</p>\n<p>For example, you can stop spending time on a category that your visitors are not interested in, and invest your time and money for the ones that work best.</p>\n<h3>6. Published at</h3>\n<p>Do your latest articles gain traction among your audience?</p>\n<p>For example, if most of your popular content was written years ago, it reveals that your latest articles are not gaining enough traction among your audience. In that case, you can focus on writing great content and promote your latest articles in your niche.</p>\n<h3>7. Tags</h3>\n<p>Unlike Categories, Tags give you more detailed insights about what works best on your site. It also helps you to come up with future blog post ideas for your site.</p>\n<h3>8. SEO Score</h3>\n<p>If you’re using the Yoast plugin for SEO, you can analyze the SEO score of your posts and pages in Google Analytics. It helps you to identify if SEO scores really matter and how these scores influence your organic traffic.</p>\n<p>You can get a data-driven report based on your SEO scores, which help you restructure your <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">SEO strategy</a> for improving organic traffic.</p>\n<h3>9. Focus Keyword</h3>\n<p>Focus Keyword is another custom dimension you can set for your site. It is also applicable only if you’re using the Yoast plugin for SEO. The Yoast plugin requires you to set a focus keyword for every post. </p>\n<p>You can identify what focus keywords are driving more organic traffic and get data-driven insights about choosing focus keywords for boosting organic traffic.</p>\n<p>We hope this guide helped you to get some insights about creating custom dimensions in Google Analytics. You may also want to see our <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/the-definitive-guide-to-google-analytics-for-publishers/\">definitive guide to Google Analytics for publishers</a>. </p>\n<p>If you liked this article, you might want to check out our guide on <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-goal-in-google-analytics-to-track-conversions/\">creating a goal to track conversions in Google Analytics</a>. And don’t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more Google Analytics tutorials.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/the-beginners-guide-to-custom-dimensions-in-google-analytics/\">The Beginners Guide to Custom Dimensions in Google Analytics</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:98:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/the-beginners-guide-to-custom-dimensions-in-google-analytics/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		